ess is more severe: communication difficulty vs interpersonal remarks. Both affect crew. C's difficulty communicating ideas could be dangerous for flight deck coordination. B's nasty remarks may be mitigated if they are occasional. Also B's weak memory for numbers could be mitigated by automation.\n\nThus provisional preference: Candidate B.\n\nWe should note uncertainties: severity of B's interpersonal issues, impact of memory weakness, unknown leadership style of A, unknown teamwork of D, unknown willingness to develop of C.\n\nWe can ask other agents for any positive attributes we lack: e.g., ask Agent 1 about any strengths for D's teamwork, or about C's reliability, etc. But we already have some from Agent 1: C is 100% reliable, creates positive atmosphere. That is a strong point. However that was not in explicit list? It was in Agent 1's internal summary, not explicit. The explicit list from Agent 1 includes \"C puts concern for others above everything\" and \"C has excellent attention skills\". Not \"100% reliable\". So we cannot use that.\n\nThus we stick with B.\n\nNow produce output."}
